Starting a New Project

1. Create Git Repository, clone repo locally, open in Cursor (start with Readme and .gitignore)
2. Business Model Canvas + Basic Product Design - example
3. Technical Design Doc - give Gemini chatbot your Product Design + the template, put in Cursor, in your repo, under /docs/technical-design-doc.md
4. To Do - ask Gemini for it, put it under /docs/todo.md (make sure Milestone 1 is just basic setup)
5. Ask Cursor to start Milestone 1
6. Go Setup your Firebase Project (stage version, then prod)
   a. Hosting, Functions, Firestore, Authentication
   b. When you setup Hosting, you’ll get a JS file with a JSON object that has a bunch of config
7. Give Gemini your JSON config, and ask it for a properly formatted .env.stage (including the VITE prefixes). Put this file in /apps/web (confirm all .env files are gitignored so they never get into git).
8. Tell Cursor you’ve set this up, and it can continue with Milestone 1
9. Try deploying to stage, test locally first if you want
10. Complete Milestone 1
11. Setup Prod, deploy to Prod
    Process per Milestone
12. Update documentation (TDD, todo, readme)
13. Clean up console logs
14. Check test coverage and run tests
15. Code organization check
16. Security check
